<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: SNES Legend Of Zelda 8 Bit Project]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11005&amp;p=125394#p125394"><![CDATA[
It's quite possible.  Several NES games have been ported to the Turbografx-16 by one person.<br /><br />The SNES is a little more complicated (as the TG-16 is more similar to the NES than the SNES is) but you can do it.<br /><br />You'll need to learn 65816 and SPC-700 assembly.  The SPC program will accept command bytes (ie:pseudo-NES-and-FDS-sound-register-writes) that your conversion program sends it, and will have to emulate the NES and FDS channels.  This is why you'll need SPC assembly in addition to 65816.<br /><br />Sound easy?  Then, get porting!  ;-D<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=355">ccovell</a> — Tue Feb 11, 2014 5:37 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
